  "background": "Unoccupied seats on flights cause airlines to lose revenue. A large airline wants to estimate its average number of unoccupied seats per flight over the past year. To achieve this, the records of 225 flights are randomly selected, and the number of unoccupied seats is noted for each sampled flight. Descriptive statistics for the data are displayed in the Minitab printout, Figure 6.7.",
